description:
&lt;p&gt;Surrey Heartlands CCG are looking for an Associate Director of Finance Acute to manage the Acute portfolio with the support of the NEL CSU. This is an interim role for 12 months to cover maternity leave. The main focus will be financial management of the IUC contract including the addition of Think 111 First, leading on the 999 contract across Kent, Surrey and Sussex, providing financial expertise in the management of the Acute contracts and supporting contract negotiations, costings, analysis and financial schedules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an ambitious vision for transformation and continuous improvement of health and care across our footprint. We are in the unique position of having secured a devolution deal, which for the first time really brings together health and social care by allowing us to commission from a single budget. We are also developing four dynamic and sustainable Integrated Care Partnerships (across East Surrey, Guildford and Waverley, North West Surrey and Surrey Downs localities) based on co-operation with our component partners, and focusing on local population needs, priorities and decision making.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, we have responsibility, delegated from NHS England, for managing Primary Care contracts across the Surrey Heartlands footprint&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will also provide support to the Surrey Downs ICP in the development and delivery of the system financial recovery plan. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for this opportunity will be a qualified CCAB Accountant with NHS experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would warmly welcome any questions about this opportunity - please contact Claire Fuller Deputy CFO Operational (details on the right), in the first instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
